Investigation timeline:
  [2026-03-15 5:59 UTC] Alert triggered — Phishing Alert - Deceptive Mail Detected fired on Felix@letsdefend.io's email inbox
  [2026-03-15 6:01 UTC] Ran URL through VirusTotal, flagged heavily by security vendors.
  [2026-03-15 6:02 UTC] Check if it was recieved by the intended recipient, it was.
  [2026-03-15 6:03 UTC] Delete it from recipients email inbox.
  [2026-03-15 6:07 UTC] Checked recipients endpoint system to see what OS they are running so I can use proper VM to analyze attachment to get C2 address.
  [2026-03-15 6:10 UTC] While looking at recipients endpoint system I see they visited the malicous URL inside the email, they may have downloaded the malware.
  [2026-03-15 6:20 UTC] Also while looking at recipients endpoint system I see they visited C2 Address
  [2026-03-15 6:21 UTC] Contain the recipients system.
  [2026-03-15 6:25 UTC] Filtering to see if any other users visit the C2 they did not. So our recipient was the only   system infected on the network.

Findings:
  An user on the company netowrk was sent a malicous phishing email. They opened it and clicked the malicous URL which downloaded malware onto their system. 

MITRE ATT&CK mapping:
  T1566.001, Phishing: Spearphishing AttachmentMalicious ZIP delivered via email
  T1204.002, User Execution: Malicious FileRecipient clicked URL and likely executed payload
  T1071.001, Application Layer Protocol: Web ProtocolsOutbound HTTP/S communication to C2
  T1105, Ingress Tool TransferMalware downloaded via malicious URL

Verdict:
  True Positive 

Response actions taken:
  Malicious email deleted from recipient inbox
  Affected endpoint isolated and contained via EDR
  Network-wide sweep performed for C2 indicator — no additional hosts identified
  Ticket escalated to Tier 2 / IR team for full remediation
  
Recommendations:

   * Could consider banning connections to C2 address, doesnt seem to be affilicated with any large telecommuniation / cloud service and has been used for abuse consistently. 
   * Add hash to process blacklist.
  * Block mail from SMTP Address.
  * Block sender domain.
  * Flag recipient to remind them of phishing and malware attacks.
